# Content Guidelines

## Articles
- Essays, perspectives, and design reflections
- Long-form Markdown or `.astro` files with frontmatter
- Use `ArticleLayout.astro`
- Frontmatter must include: `title`, `description`, `pubDate`, `tags`, `author`

## Case Studies
- Structured breakdowns of professional work
- Use `CaseStudyLayout.astro`
- Frontmatter includes:
  - `client`, `industry`, `duration`, `challenge`, `solution`, `results`
- Use semantic headings (`## Challenge`, `## Solution`, etc.)
- Write in past tense, professional tone

## Scratch Notes
- Experiments, code play, creative technology
- Use `ScratchLayout.astro` or embedded `.astro` components
- Use tags like: `processing`, `d3js`, `python`, `micropi`, `gcode`, `css`
- Add metadata to enable sorting (e.g. `technology`, `pubDate`, `title`)
- You may embed canvas, iframe, or SVG directly

## Style Tips
- Keep headings consistent
- Use semantic HTML in markdown (avoid deeply nested divs)
- Don't overuse blockquotes or italics
- Articles should end with a takeaway or invitation to reflect
- Scratch posts can include code blocks, visuals, and links to repos
